WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.705 --> 00:00:14.227
So I've been thinking about the difference between
我一直在思考下面两者的区别，

2
00:00:14.227 --> 00:00:17.361
the résumé virtues and  the eulogy virtues.
简历美德和悼词美德。

3
00:00:17.361 --> 00:00:20.263
The résumé virtues are the ones you put on your résumé,
简历美德是指那些你自己会写在简历上的优点，

4
00:00:20.263 --> 00:00:23.729
which are the skills  you bring to the marketplace.
这是一种在市场中生存的技能。

5
00:00:23.729 --> 00:00:25.467
The eulogy virtues are the ones
悼词美德是指那些会在

6
00:00:25.467 --> 00:00:26.949
that get mentioned in the eulogy,
你的悼词中，别人提到的话。

7
00:00:26.949 --> 00:00:29.887
which are deeper: who are you,  in your depth,
哪一个更深刻：从内心深处来讲，哪一个才是你。

8
00:00:29.887 --> 00:00:31.663
what is the nature of your relationships,
在人际关系中，你的本质是什么，

9
00:00:31.663 --> 00:00:35.227
are you bold, loving, dependable, consistency?
大胆的？深情的？值得信任的？还是稳重的？

10
00:00:35.227 --> 00:00:36.721
And most of us, including  me, would say
包括我自己在内的大多说人会说，

11
00:00:36.721 --> 00:00:39.937
that the eulogy virtues are the more important of the virtues.
悼词美德会更加重要。

12
00:00:39.947 --> 00:00:42.020
But at least in my case,  are they the ones that
但是至少从我的角度来说，他们是

13
00:00:42.020 --> 00:00:44.822
I think about the most?  And the answer is no.
我认为的最重要的那个吗？答案是否定的。

14
00:00:44.822 --> 00:00:47.115
So I've been thinking about that problem,
所以我正在思考一个问题，

15
00:00:47.115 --> 00:00:48.283
and a thinker who has  helped me think about it
并且一个思想家也在帮助我思考，

16
00:00:48.283 --> 00:00:49.896
is a guy named Joseph Soloveitchik, who was a rabbi
叫做约瑟夫，过去是一个犹太学者，

17
00:00:49.896 --> 00:00:53.266
who wrote a book called "The Lonely Man Of Faith" in 1965.
在1965年著有《有信仰的孤独人》。

18
00:00:53.266 --> 00:00:56.586
Soloveitchik said there are two sides of our natures,
索罗维奇可说到我们的本质可以分为两面，

19
00:00:55.966 --> 00:00:58.976
which he called Adam I and Adam II.
他称之为亚当一号以及亚当二号。

20
00:00:58.976 --> 00:01:00.708
Adam I is the worldly, ambitious,
亚当一号是世俗的，雄心勃勃的，

21
00:01:00.708 --> 00:01:02.931
external side of our nature.
是我们本质外在的一面。

22
00:01:02.931 --> 00:01:05.004
He wants to build, create, create companies,
这一面想要去建造，去创造，创造公司，

23
00:01:05.004 --> 00:01:06.550
create innovation.
创造革新。

24
00:01:06.550 --> 00:01:09.288
Adam II is the humble side of our nature.
亚当二号则是本质中谦逊的那一面。

25
00:01:09.288 --> 00:01:12.105
Adam II wants not only  to do good but to be good,
亚当二号要求不仅要做好事，并且要成为好人，

26
00:01:12.105 --> 00:01:14.052
to live in a way internally
去以一种内在的方式生活，

27
00:01:14.052 --> 00:01:17.855
that honors God, creation and our possibilities.
去尊敬上帝，创作，以及自我的责任。

28
00:01:17.855 --> 00:01:19.743
Adam I wants to conquer the world.
亚当一号想要征服这个世界。

29
00:01:19.743 --> 00:01:22.507
Adam II wants to hear  a calling and obey the world.
亚当二号想要倾听这个世界的呼唤并且遵循这个世界。

30
00:01:22.507 --> 00:01:24.995
Adam I savors accomplishment.
亚当一号尽情享受那种成就感。

31
00:01:24.995 --> 00:01:27.677
Adam II savors inner  consistency and strength.
亚当二号则享受内在的融合和赐予的力量。

32
00:01:27.677 --> 00:01:30.420
Adam I asks how things work.
亚当一号询问事情怎么运转。

33
00:01:30.420 --> 00:01:32.738
Adam II asks why we're here.
亚当二号则关心我们为什么在这里。

34
00:01:32.738 --> 00:01:34.842
Adam I's motto is "success."
亚当一号的座右铭是“成功”。

35
00:01:34.842 --> 00:01:39.088
Adam II's motto is "love, redemption and return."
亚当二号的座右铭是“爱，拯救和回报”。

36
00:01:39.088 --> 00:01:40.938
And Soloveitchik argued  that these two sides
同时，索罗维奇可也思考过我们

37
00:01:40.938 --> 00:01:43.586
of our nature are  at war with each other.
这两种感情的相互斗争。

38
00:01:43.586 --> 00:01:45.650
We live in perpetual self-confrontation
我们生活在一个不断进行自我抗争，

39
00:01:45.650 --> 00:01:48.914
between the external success and the internal value.
夹杂在外在的成功和内在的价值之中。

40
00:01:48.914 --> 00:01:51.398
And the tricky thing,  I'd say, about these
我认为更有趣的是，

41
00:01:51.398 --> 00:01:53.090
two sides of our nature is they work
我们的两种本质，

42
00:01:53.090 --> 00:01:55.500
by different logics.
依照不同的逻辑运作。

43
00:01:55.500 --> 00:01:57.734
The external logic is  an economic logic:
外在逻辑方法是经济学的逻辑方式：

44
00:01:57.734 --> 00:02:01.200
input leads to output,  risk leads to reward.
投入产出模式和风险回报模式。

45
00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:02.976
The internal side of our nature
我们内在的本质

46
00:02:02.976 --> 00:02:06.397
is a moral logic and  often an inverse logic.
是一种道德上的逻辑，通常是一种逆向逻辑。

47
00:02:06.397 --> 00:02:08.271
You have to give to receive.
你不得不用你的付出去获得。

48
00:02:08.271 --> 00:02:09.987
You have to surrender  to something outside yourself
你不得不先放弃你自身的外在的一些东西

49
00:02:09.987 --> 00:02:12.269
to gain strength within yourself.
去获得自己内在的力量。

50
00:02:12.269 --> 00:02:14.590
You have to conquer the desire to get what you want.
你需要克服你想要的东西的欲望。

51
00:02:14.590 --> 00:02:17.381
In order to fulfill yourself, you have to forget yourself.
为了使自己满足，你需要先忘记你自己。

52
00:02:17.381 --> 00:02:21.693
In order to find yourself,  you have to lose yourself.
为了去找到自我，你需要先失去自我。

53
00:02:21.693 --> 00:02:24.629
We happen to live in a society  that favors Adam I,
我们碰巧生活在一个支持亚当一号的社会中，

54
00:02:24.629 --> 00:02:26.869
and often neglects Adam II.
并且经常会忽视亚当二号。

55
00:02:26.869 --> 00:02:30.101
And the problem is, that turns you into a shrewd animal
那么问题就是，这会使你成为一个精明的动物，

56
00:02:30.101 --> 00:02:31.658
who treats life as a game,
一个把生活当做游戏的人，

57
00:02:31.658 --> 00:02:34.383
and you become a cold,  calculating creature
并且你会成为一个无情的，爱计较的人，

58
00:02:34.383 --> 00:02:37.189
who slips into a sort of mediocrity
最后堕落为庸人这一类，

59
00:02:37.189 --> 00:02:38.649
where you realize there's a difference
直到那个时候你才意识到欲望里的自己

60
00:02:38.649 --> 00:02:41.221
between your desired  self and your actual self.
和真实的自己是有区别的。

61
00:02:41.221 --> 00:02:45.194
You're not earning the sort of eulogy you want,
你并没有得到你想要的悼词，

62
00:02:45.194 --> 00:02:46.754
you hope someone will give to you.
你希望别人可以给你。

63
00:02:46.754 --> 00:02:48.480
You don't have the  depth of conviction.
你没有坚定的信仰。

64
00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:51.017
You don't have an emotional sonorousness.
你没有丰富的情绪。

65
00:02:51.017 --> 00:02:52.786
You don't have  commitment to tasks
你并没有一个要花费一生的

66
00:02:52.786 --> 00:02:56.000
that would take more than a lifetime to commit.
时间去实现的承诺。

67
00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:59.447
I was reminded of a common response through history
纵观历史我得到了一个相同的回答，

68
00:02:59.447 --> 00:03:02.209
of how you build a solid Adam II,
是告诉你怎样去建立一个坚固的亚当二号，

69
00:03:02.209 --> 00:03:04.219
how you build a depth of character.
怎样去塑造一个有深度的性格。

70
00:03:04.219 --> 00:03:06.944
Through history, people  have gone back
回首过往，人们可以

71
00:03:06.944 --> 00:03:08.830
into their own pasts,
看到自己的过去，

72
00:03:08.830 --> 00:03:11.080
sometimes to a precious  time in their life,
有时候是生命中很珍贵的某个时刻，

73
00:03:11.080 --> 00:03:12.539
to their childhood,
有时候是童年，

74
00:03:12.539 --> 00:03:16.505
and often, the mind  gravitates in the past
更多的，会吸引你的是

75
00:03:16.505 --> 00:03:17.893
to a moment of shame,
那些让你感到羞耻的瞬间，

76
00:03:17.893 --> 00:03:20.820
some sin committed,  some act of selfishness,
一些犯错的时候，比如一些自私的举动，

77
00:03:20.820 --> 00:03:23.110
an act of omission, of shallowness,
一些欠考虑或者肤浅的行为，

78
00:03:23.110 --> 00:03:25.853
the sin of anger, the sin of self-pity,
一些愤怒时犯的过错，一些自怜自哀时的行为，

79
00:03:25.853 --> 00:03:29.438
trying to be a people-pleaser,  a lack of courage.
总是去迎合别人或者缺乏勇气的时候。

80
00:03:29.438 --> 00:03:34.133
Adam I is built by  building on your strengths.
亚当一号是建立在堆砌你的优点上的。

81
00:03:34.133 --> 00:03:38.229
Adam II is built by fighting  your weaknesses.
亚当二号是建立在打败你的缺点上的。

82
00:03:38.229 --> 00:03:41.087
You go into yourself,  you find the sin
当你走入自己的内心，你会发现那些在你生命中

83
00:03:41.087 --> 00:03:42.759
which you've committed over and again through your life,
犯了一次又一次的错误，

84
00:03:42.759 --> 00:03:44.560
your signature sin
你最不能忘记的那个过错

85
00:03:44.560 --> 00:03:47.251
out of which the others emerge,
会区别于其它的那些过错，

86
00:03:47.251 --> 00:03:50.115
and you fight that sin and you wrestle with that sin,
你会和那个过错做斗争，去努力克服那个过错，

87
00:03:50.115 --> 00:03:53.251
and out of that wrestling,  that suffering,
当你从那些斗争和苦难中重生的时候，

88
00:03:53.251 --> 00:03:56.869
then a depth of character is constructed.
也就是一个有深度的性格建立的时候。

89
00:03:56.869 --> 00:03:58.771
And we're often not taught to recognize
同时，我没并没有经常被教导

90
00:03:58.771 --> 00:03:59.907
the sin in ourselves,
怎么认识到自己的过错，

91
00:03:59.907 --> 00:04:01.755
in that we're not taught in this culture
在现在的文化中我们也没有

92
00:04:01.755 --> 00:04:03.702
how to wrestle with it,
被教导怎么去和它们斗争，

93
00:04:03.702 --> 00:04:06.375
how to confront it,  and how to combat it.
怎么去面对它们并，如何它们斗争。

94
00:04:06.375 --> 00:04:09.705
We live in a culture  with an Adam I mentality
我们生活在一个有着亚当一号心理的社会中，

95
00:04:09.705 --> 00:04:12.874
where we're inarticulate  about Adam II.
在这里我们很难表达亚当二号的思想。

96
00:04:12.874 --> 00:04:14.530
Finally, Reinhold Niebuhr
最后，莱因霍尔德·尼布尔

97
00:04:14.530 --> 00:04:16.665
summed up the confrontation, the fully lived
用这种方式总结了生活中

98
00:04:16.665 --> 00:04:20.218
Adam I and Adam II life, this way:
亚当一号和亚当二号完全对立的这种存在：

99
00:04:20.218 --> 00:04:23.480
"Nothing that is worth doing can be achieved in our lifetime;
“没有一件值得一做的事情，可以在你的一生中完成；

100
00:04:23.480 --> 00:04:25.862
therefore we must  be saved by hope.
因此我们必须用希望来拯救。

101
00:04:25.862 --> 00:04:28.968
Nothing which is true or beautiful or good makes
没有一样真实或者美丽的东西，

102
00:04:28.968 --> 00:04:31.924
complete sense in any immediate context of history;
可以在历史的一瞬展现它的华彩；

103
00:04:31.924 --> 00:04:34.602
therefore we must be saved by faith.
因此我们必须用信仰来救赎。

104
00:04:34.602 --> 00:04:38.492
Nothing we do, however virtuous, can be accomplished alone;
没有一件事情，哪怕它是美好的，我们可以独自完成；

105
00:04:38.492 --> 00:04:41.538
therefore we must  be saved by love.
因此我们必须用爱来拯救。

106
00:04:41.538 --> 00:04:43.975
No virtuous act is quite as virtuous
没有什么善良的行为是完全的善，

107
00:04:43.975 --> 00:04:47.961
from the standpoint of our friend or foe as from our own standpoint.
不论是从朋友，敌人，或者我们自身的角度都是这样。

108
00:04:47.961 --> 00:04:50.788
Therefore we must be saved  by that final form of love,
因此我们必须被完全的爱来拯救，

109
00:04:50.788 --> 00:04:52.424
which is forgiveness.”
也就是用宽容。“

110
00:04:52.424 --> 00:04:54.500
Thanks.
谢谢大家。

111
00:04:54.500 --> 00:04:56.218
(Applause)
（掌声）